content.problemStatement:
A girl counts on her fingers by counting 1 on her thumb, 2 on her index finger, 3 on her middle
finger, 4 on her ring finger, and 5 on her little finger. Then she continues the other way, counting 6
on her ring finger, 7 on her middle finger, 8 on her index finger, and 9 on her thumb. Then she
continues the other way, counting 10 on her index finger, 11 on her middle finger, 12 on her ring
finger, and 13 on her little finger. She continues in this way indefinitely as shown in the image
below:

![image](https://s3.amazonaws.com/hr-assets/0/1751976253-9789b30239-Countnumbers.png)

You are given a function,
int CountingOnFingers(int n);
int CountingOnFingers(int n);
static int CountingOnFingers(int n){}
static int CountingOnFingers(int n){}
def CountingOnFingers(n):
The function takes a number 'n' as input and returns which finger the girl will be on when her count
reaches 'n'. Assume 'n' >= 1. If she will be on her thumb, then return 1, if index finger then return
2, if middle finger then return 3, if ring finger then return 4 and if little finger then return 5.
